Yeah... The logic in not re-using a worker is that the pattern matching aspect made it both difficult and somewhat inconsistent due to the dynamic nature of the situation, hence the use of the "default" worker for these.

We now have the functionality to handle this, but it is still a performance hit and in most cases enablereuse should be disabled. But we still make that an admin decision, and I think that's still the right move.

Cheers!

> On Oct 6, 2022, at 11:32 AM, Eric Covener <covener@gmail.com> wrote:
